Dear Professor Kuhlmann

I should actually say good evening, because I'm in Europe right now, and the current time is 11:30 p.m. I came here to support the customer's business. 

My name is Hu Wenbin, from China. I graduated from Hangzhou Dianzi University in 2019 with a master's degree in control engineering. After graduation, I have been engaged in software development related work in Huawei Technologies Co., LTD. (the most famous communication company in China and a mobile phone manufacturer). My graduate thesis is the prediction of epileptic seizure based on machine learning, which I believe matches your direction
My partner, Deutsche Telekom, bought some of our company's products such as servers and some other solution products, which need the support of engineers. At present, my main job is to maintain the stability of the live network, update and upgrade the version of the live network system, and solve customers' problems. I've written code, I've done testing, I've done pretty much anything related to software development.

